{
  "nbformat": 4,
  "nbformat_minor": 5,
  "metadata": {
    "kernelspec": {
      "name": "maxima",
      "display_name": "Maxima",
      "language": "maxima"
    },
    "aximar": {}
  },
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Nonlinear Equations and Least-Squares Fitting\n\nSolve systems of nonlinear equations with `np_fsolve` and fit overdetermined systems with `np_lsq_nonlinear`. Both wrap Fortran MINPACK.\n\nTwo calling conventions:\n\n- **Expression mode** — write equations symbolically; the Jacobian is computed via `diff()` and compiled automatically\n- **Function mode** — pass a callback `f(x)` taking a 1D ndarray; the Jacobian is approximated by finite differences",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "load(\"numerics\")$\nload(\"numerics-optimize\")$\nload(\"ax-plots\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 10,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 1. Scalar Root Finding\n\nFind $\\sqrt{2}$ by solving $x^2 - 2 = 0$.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "[x_opt, rnorm, info] : np_fsolve([x^2 - 2], [x], [1.0]);\nprint(\"x =\", np_ref(x_opt, 0), \" residual =\", rnorm, \" info =\", info)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 11,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "[ndarray(\\#\\<ndarray\\ 1\\ DOUBLE\\-FLOAT\\ \\(1\\)\\>),8.881784197001252e-16,1]\nx = 1.4142135623730947  residual = 8.881784197001252e-16  info = 1"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 2. System of Equations\n\nFind the intersection of the unit circle $x^2 + y^2 = 1$ and the line $y = x$ in the first quadrant.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "[xy_opt, rnorm2, info2] : np_fsolve(\n  [x^2 + y^2 - 1, y - x], [x, y], [0.5, 0.5]);\n\nprint(\"Intersection:\", np_to_list(xy_opt))$\nprint(\"Residual:\", rnorm2)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 12,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "[ndarray(\\#\\<ndarray\\ 2\\ DOUBLE\\-FLOAT\\ \\(2\\)\\>),4.440892098500626e-16,1]\nIntersection: [0.7071067811865474,0.7071067811865474]\nResidual: 4.440892098500626e-16"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Visualize */\nax_draw2d(\n  color=\"blue\", line_width=2, name=\"x^2 + y^2 = 1\",\n  parametric(cos(s), sin(s), s, 0, float(2*%pi)),\n  color=\"orange\", line_width=2, name=\"y = x\",\n  explicit(x, x, -1.5, 1.5),\n  color=\"red\", marker_size=8, name=\"Solution\",\n  points([[np_ref(xy_opt, 0), np_ref(xy_opt, 1)]]),\n  title=\"Circle-Line Intersection\",\n  xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"y\", grid=true, showlegend=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 13,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
