    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 3. Chemical Equilibrium\n\nA reaction $A \\rightleftharpoons 2B$ has equilibrium constant $K = [B]^2 / [A]$. Starting from $[A]_0 = 1$, $[B]_0 = 0$, find the equilibrium concentrations (conservation: $[A] + [B]/2 = 1$).",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "K_eq : 0.5$\n[conc, rn, inf_eq] : np_fsolve(\n  [cb^2/ca - K_eq, ca + cb/2 - 1],\n  [ca, cb], [0.8, 0.4])$\n\nprint(\"[A] =\", np_ref(conc, 0))$\nprint(\"[B] =\", np_ref(conc, 1))$\nprint(\"Check K:\", np_ref(conc, 1)^2 / np_ref(conc, 0))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 14,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "[A] = 0.7034648345913732\n[B] = 0.5930703308172536\nCheck K: 0.5"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 4. Nonlinear Least Squares: Curve Fitting\n\nFit $y = a \\cdot e^{b x}$ to noisy data using `np_lsq_nonlinear`. We write one residual expression per data point.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Generate noisy exponential data: y = 2*exp(0.3*x) + noise */\nn_pts : 20$\nx_data : np_linspace(0.0, 3.0, n_pts)$\ny_true : np_scale(2.0, np_exp(np_scale(0.3, x_data)))$\ny_data : np_add(y_true, np_scale(0.15, np_randn([n_pts])))$\n\n/* Build residual list: a*exp(b*x_i) - y_i for each point */\nresiduals : makelist(\n  a_fit * exp(b_fit * np_ref(x_data, i)) - np_ref(y_data, i),\n  i, 0, n_pts - 1)$\n\n[ab_opt, res_norm, lsq_info] : np_lsq_nonlinear(\n  residuals, [a_fit, b_fit], [1.0, 0.1])$\n\na_found : np_ref(ab_opt, 0)$\nb_found : np_ref(ab_opt, 1)$\nprint(\"Fitted: a =\", a_found, \" b =\", b_found)$\nprint(\"True:   a = 2, b = 0.3\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 15,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Fitted: a = 1.9740112229040165  b = 0.30184405403101644\nTrue:   a = 2, b = 0.3"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "ax_draw2d(\n  color=\"red\", marker_size=5, name=\"Noisy data\",\n  points(np_to_list(x_data), np_to_list(y_data)),\n  color=\"blue\", line_width=2, name=\"Fitted curve\",\n  explicit(a_found * exp(b_found * x), x, 0, 3),\n  color=\"gray\", dash=\"dash\", name=\"True curve\",\n  explicit(2 * exp(0.3 * x), x, 0, 3),\n  title=\"Nonlinear Least Squares Fit\",\n  xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"y\", grid=true, showlegend=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 16,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
